  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "In Orlando, June typically marks the beginning of the summer season, characterized by warm temperatures and increased humidity. Average high temperatures in June range from the mid-80s to low 90s Fahrenheit (around 29-34\u00b0C), while nighttime lows are generally in the upper 60s to low 70s Fahrenheit (about 20-24\u00b0C). June is also the start of the Atlantic hurricane season, leading to an increased likelihood of afternoon thunderstorms, which can be frequent but often brief.\n\nIn August, the weather in Orlando remains quite warm and humid, with similar high temperatures ranging from the upper 80s to low 90s Fahrenheit (around 31-34\u00b0C) and nighttime lows generally in the low 70s (about 21-24\u00b0C). August is typically one of the hottest months of the year and can also see frequent afternoon thunderstorms, sometimes more intense than in June. The humidity levels in August tend to be higher, making it feel warmer than in June.\n\nIn summary, both June and August in Orlando are warm and humid, with high temperatures and chances of thunderstorms, but August can be slightly hotter and more humid compared to June.",
